    h1: 'Business Account vs Personal Account',
    intro: `Navigating the world of banking can be complex, especially when you're running a business. A fundamental decision for any entrepreneur or small business owner in the UK is whether to use a personal bank account or a dedicated business bank account. While both serve the primary function of managing money, their underlying purposes, features, and legal implications differ significantly. Understanding these distinctions is crucial for maintaining financial clarity, ensuring compliance with UK regulations, and fostering the professional growth of your enterprise. This comprehensive guide will delve into the core differences between business and personal bank accounts, exploring their unique characteristics, legal requirements, and the practical benefits of choosing the right option for your specific circumstances.`,
