        heading: `What is the Current Account Switch Service (CASS)?`,
        content: `The Current Account Switch Service (CASS) is a free, trusted, and independent service in the UK that makes switching bank accounts simple, secure, and guaranteed. Launched in 2013 and operated by Pay.UK, CASS was introduced to increase competition in the banking sector by removing the traditional barriers and anxieties associated with changing banks. Historically, businesses were reluctant to switch providers due to the fear of missed payments, administrative headaches, and potential financial losses. CASS was designed specifically to address and eliminate these concerns.

For businesses, CASS takes the administrative burden out of moving your financial operations from one bank or building society to another. Whether you are a sole trader, a small-to-medium enterprise (SME), or a charity, the service ensures that your transition is handled entirely by your new bank. Over 50 UK banks and building societies participate in the scheme, meaning you have a wide variety of options when looking for a business account that better suits your needs. This extensive participation covers the vast majority of the UK banking market, from traditional high street banks to modern digital challenger banks.

The core of the service is the Current Account Switch Guarantee. This guarantee provides absolute peace of mind by ensuring that your switch will be completed in just seven working days. Furthermore, it promises that all your incoming and outgoing payments will be automatically transferred, and you will be refunded for any interest or charges incurred if anything goes wrong during the process. This guarantee is the cornerstone of the service, providing a risk-free environment for businesses to seek out better financial products.`
